      <title>TSS spells - comments and suggestions. [FTAO: anyone who has authority to change spell data]</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Shadowknights&amp;message.id=5746#M5746</link>
      <description>A comment was made in a thread on veterans forum that if anyone thinks spells need "fixing" or tweaking that details should be given as to what the problem is and why its a problem.&lt;br&gt;I've also included some suggestions.&lt;br&gt;hopfully I've articulated my thoughts well enough to show why i think changes are needed for some SK spells.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/spell.html?id=10233&amp;amp;source=Live" target="_blank"&gt;Bond of the Blacktalon&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;there is no way to focus or crit the heal portion of this spell.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;this&#xD;
means that from the moment you buy it, it's less efficient then a&#xD;
direct tap so long as you have crit aa and/or a magic damage focus.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;this goes for all sk tap over time spells since PoP atleast [didnt look back past that]&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;but I'll deal with the numbers from TSS [and also include the numbers from the lvl 70 direct tap.]&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Bond of the Blacktalon&lt;br&gt;Decrease Hitpoints by 155 per tick&lt;br&gt;Mana: 507&lt;br&gt;cast time: 3 [1.6 iirc with hybrid spell haste]&lt;br&gt;Duration: 7 ticks.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;155 x 7 = 1085 dmg/heal&lt;br&gt;1085/507 = 2.1 hp per mana&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;there is no way to focus the heal portion, either duration or potency.&lt;br&gt;the heal portion can not crit and a dmg crit does not crit the heal because the heal is a "recorse".&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/spell.html?id=10327&amp;amp;source=Live" target="_blank"&gt;Touch of Severan&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Decrease Hitpoints by 1238&lt;br&gt;Mana: 719&lt;br&gt;cast time 1.5&lt;br&gt;recast: 12&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;1238/719 = 1.7 hp per mana&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;but &lt;br&gt;a crit blast doubles the heals&lt;br&gt;a crit heal obviously also doubles the heal&lt;br&gt;a crit blast and a crit heal can occure on the same cast for quadruple heal.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;with&#xD;
maxed crit blast and heal AA there is a 45% chance of a crit blast or a&#xD;
crit heal and a 2% chance of a crit blast plus a crit heal so far as I&#xD;
can tell.&lt;br&gt;so with those AA about 45% of the casts will yield a 3.4hp per mana ratio and 2% will be 6.8 hp per mana.&lt;br&gt;that averages out [if my math is right] to 2.48 hp per mana on every cast. [average over time]&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;thats without taking focii into account.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;I&#xD;
have a 60% magic focii, which acts at 42% on lvl 75 spells, the average&#xD;
percentage is 21%, so each DD life tap is on average 21% larger to&#xD;
begin with.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;1238*121% = 1498 [1497.9 to be exact i think]&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;1498/719 = 2 hp per mana. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;using the same method to factor in the crits as i did above i get on average &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;about 45% will be 4hp per mana&lt;br&gt;about 2% will be 8 hp per mana.&lt;br&gt;the average I think will be 2.92 hp per mana [I think]&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;so&#xD;
what possable reason could I have for using a 2.1hp per mana tap over&#xD;
time that takes 7 ticks to do the full amount? [how many mobs even last&#xD;
7 ticks + the time it takes to build enough agro at the begining ?]&lt;br&gt;whats more once you use that spell, that mob can not be messed for 7 ticks should the need arise [rare as it might be].&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;"but", i hear you say, "you could have the DD tap and the tap over time memmed...&lt;br&gt;I&#xD;
could, or I could just mem my lvl 70 DD tap instead [and not I dont&#xD;
have room for 3 taps and whats more with 2 DD taps loaded they can&#xD;
almost be chain cast]&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;lets look briefly at the lvl 70 tap&#xD;
efficiency, I wont do all the math but it should be evident from the&#xD;
base ratio that even with crit aa and no focii its more efficient&#xD;
aswell.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/spell.html?id=5338&amp;amp;source=Live" target="_blank"&gt;Touch of the Devourer&#xD;
      &lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;Decrease Hitpoints by 740&lt;br&gt;Mana: 448&lt;br&gt;cast time: 3&lt;br&gt;recast: 10&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;base ratio:1.65 hp per mana.&lt;br&gt;considering the lvl 75 tap is 1.7 I'm sure its clear&amp;nbsp; the lvl 70 tap at 1.65 will also be far superior to the TSS tap over time.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;I&#xD;
didnt bother laying out the Hp per second ratings as it should be clear&#xD;
that DD taps blow our tap over time out of the water by far.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;also&#xD;
i did NOT include the recorse from Remorseless Demeanor which adds from&#xD;
50% at rank 1 to 80% at rank 2 to 100% at rank 3 to the potency of DD&#xD;
life taps but not to tap over time recorses.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Solution!&lt;br&gt;ok to be useful this tap over time needs to fill 1 of 2 roles.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;it either needs to be EXTREAMLY efficient or it needs to do A LOT of healing.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;also&#xD;
there really isn't any point to having it heal LESS then the DD tap&#xD;
when even if one goes OOM its only 3.5 mins to med completely.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;now to specifics.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;if it were up to me, this is what I'd do.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;version 1 which provide for a significant amount of healing for comparitive efficiency to a DD life tap with AA but no foci.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Bond of the Blacktalon [new]&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
Decrease Hitpoints by 666 per tick&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
Mana: 2264&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
cast time: 3 [1.6 iirc with hybrid spell haste]&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
Duration: 10 ticks.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;2.5 hp per mana.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;OR&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;version&#xD;
2 which should be on average as efficient as a DD tap with AA and a&#xD;
decent focii. though the DD tap will win out for high-end players with&#xD;
50% or better focii.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Bond of the Blacktalon [new MkII]&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
Decrease Hitpoints by 310 per tick&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
Mana: 861&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
cast time: 3 [1.6 iirc with hybrid spell haste]&lt;br&gt;&#xD;
Duration: 10 ticks.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;3.6hp per mana.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;either of those 2 changes would make the tap over time compeditive with the direct tap.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;also&#xD;
at 10 ticks duration the healing increase should be larger then the&#xD;
damage increase given that most fights dont last long enough for the&#xD;
full duration of the damage portion to take effect.&lt;br&gt;but life taps are about healing more then about DPS.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr size="2" width="100%"&gt;now for more things i think need looking at, or atleast if who ever looks after spells could perhaps comment on why they cant/shouldnt be tweaked that wuld be great.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;SK disease based "Spears", they either need a&#xD;
significant resist mod [like -150] or a disease debuffs needs to be&#xD;
added to SK terror spells.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;because Disease is the lease debuffed resist, being that it is not in the malo/mala line of spells.&lt;br&gt;and not often having that resist debuffed hurts the usefulness of the spear line, that combined with the new TSS spear "&lt;a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/spell.html?id=10288&amp;amp;source=Live" target="_blank"&gt;&#xD;
            Rotroot Spear&lt;/a&gt;"&#xD;
that shares a recast timer with our other spears, so we have a DD thats&#xD;
prone to being resisted due to lack of debuffs and also not usable in&#xD;
combination with other lower level spears where the OoW spear was&#xD;
usable with other lower level spears except the ancient from GoD iirc.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;the&#xD;
spear isn't useless but its far from "desirable" when a small tweak&#xD;
like giving it a resist mod OR giving SK's a disease debuff on our&#xD;
terrors would make it much more useful.&lt;br&gt;I for one hardly ever mem a spear, mostly its more efficient just to use a life tap.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr size="2" width="100%"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/spell.html?id=10276&amp;amp;source=Live" target="_blank"&gt;&#xD;
            Drink of Decomposition&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;sort of speaks for itself I think.&lt;br&gt;but I'll make the point anyway.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Vald, frostcrypt and ashengate dont have any plant NPCs so far as I've seen.&lt;br&gt;most of EQ doesnt have any plant NPCs in high level XP zones.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;yes&#xD;
a druid could turn some mobs into plants, thought many are uneffected,&#xD;
such as undead and giants, which make up the majority portion of high&#xD;
end TSS content.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;also&lt;br&gt;Limit: Resist(Fire allowed)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;so&#xD;
the 3% incrreased damage doesnt work on my magic based life tap or any other spell I have anyway,&#xD;
so that means that unless i have a heavly fire based caster DPS team in&#xD;
my group that that spell wont be used.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;ah yes, a shaman could use &lt;a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/spell.html?id=9999&amp;amp;source=Live" target="_blank"&gt;&#xD;
            Feralize&lt;/a&gt;&#xD;
...but wait ...if i have a shaman in my group that means I either have&#xD;
a primary healer, such as&amp;nbsp; a druid or a cleric and thus with a primary&#xD;
and a back up I wont be needing to use life taps to patch heal myself &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;OR&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;the&#xD;
shaman is going to be so busy debuffing, slowing .etc and then healing&#xD;
me, the tank, that they wont have time to waste casting a spell so I&#xD;
can use one specific sort of life tap which is only marginally more&#xD;
efficient then my normal life taps.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;so this makes the Sk plant only life tap useless mostly.&lt;br&gt;i have rank 2 and have never cast it, infact I've not fought a plant mob since I got the spell many weeks ago.&lt;br&gt;and&#xD;
with the ratity of plant mobs why would I have it memmed wasting a&#xD;
spell gem of which I have far more usefulls that I dont have room to&#xD;
keep memmed?&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr size="2" width="100%"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;I'd actually like to see the plant only life tap deleted and replaced with an ATK tap.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;not a DD + recorse but a spell that lowers the ATK of my target and increases my own or even my groups atk.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
