    <item>
      <title>New mitigation type disc idea for Shadowknights</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Shadowknights&amp;message.id=5613#M5613</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;This was posted on Evilgamer.net ( &amp;nbsp;&lt;A href="http://www.evilgamer.net/forums/showthread.php?t=874" target=_blank&gt;http://www.evilgamer.net/forums/showthread.php?t=874&lt;/A&gt;&amp;nbsp;) and got some good feedback. Posting it here to get a bit more.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Since one of our main rolls in current content seems to be CCing / offtanking several mobs at the same time and SOE seems to be giving us spells that are forcing SK's go down that road. IE Dreadgaze (aggroing many mobs at once), D-Skin (defensive rune proc - the more mobs that are attacking you the more it goes off) I propose adding a Soulshield type disc, that scales in effectiveness and power based on the number of mobs that have you first on their hate list!&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Could call it Malevolent Guard ,or some wierd name like that.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;It would work like this...&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;1 mob has you first on hate list, you use the disc, you get 18 seconds of 15%mitigation to inc melee dmg.&lt;BR&gt;2-3 mobs have you first on hate list, you use the disc, you get 30 seconds of 30% inc melee dmg mitigation.&lt;BR&gt;4-6 mobs have you on hate list, you use the disc, you get 48 seconds of 40%mitigation to inc melee dmg.&lt;BR&gt;6+ mobs have you on hate list, you use the disc, you get 1 minute with 45% mitigation to inc melee dmg (cap it there)&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Give it a 30 minute re-use.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Some of the issues/worries that came up were...&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Q: "Whats stopping an SK from aggroing many green con mobs then engaging a raid boss with the disc capped out in power?"&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;A: The lack of many green con mobs in high end raid zones. Also you could put a level floor on the mobs that would effect the disc. For instance mobs&amp;nbsp;3 levels or more below the SK, would not effect the disc power or duration&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Q: This would make SK's overpowered in PvP&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;A: The disc power would only increase by having NPC's attacking the SK that used the disc. Would not effect PC's&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Q: "more realistically, aggroing 5 DBs, mezzing them, and &lt;I&gt;then&lt;/I&gt; engaging a red boss mob, which would still cap the disc?"&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;A: Because, the raid would still be better off having a warrior tank one hard hitting raid mob with defensive disc going, than the raid would be having to CC 5 adds, while at the same time having the SK tank a hard hitting raid mob.&lt;!--  / message  --&gt;&lt;!--  sig  --&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;This would be great, because it would really strengthen our CC/offtank power, coupled with Dread Gaze and D-skin. &lt;STRONG&gt;While not&amp;nbsp;encroaching&amp;nbsp;on warriors&lt;/STRONG&gt; being able to tank hard hitting boss mobs. If you think its too overpowered, just scale down the duration and mitigation&amp;nbsp;percentages utill you think its fair/doable. What do you guys think?&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;!--  / message  --&gt;&lt;!--  sig  --&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
